* Speaker coordinator - Finding speakers and making sure that they're where they need to be when it comes time to speak (supervised by the main speaker manager, <PERSON>).
* Talk Timing - Keep track of time during talks, and warn speakers with signs at certain points (managed by the main speaker manager, <PERSON>). New additional task: sound the triangle a few minutes before the session starts, to let people in the break area know the next talk will start soon.
* Floaters - Other duties as assigned. Assist with odds and ends requests from other volunteers and organizers as well as answering questions; overall, being generally helpful. You can watch talks during this shift, as long as I can contact you if needed. Do make sure you stay in / very near the venue.
* Unconference / Job Fair - Camping out in the unconference / job fair area downstairs, keeping the place in order, updating unconference room schedule, assisting with questions, and so on (managed by the unconference coordinator, <PERSON>).
* Social event - making sure everyone entering has a badge or wristband, and handing out wristbands to people with badges. This likely does not need two people all the time, but having two people assigned makes it easier to do things like getting drinks.

